The paper focuses on understanding the information encoded in word embeddings, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) research. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates the quality and characteristics of different embeddings, which falls under the scope of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also discuss the impact of varying the number of dimensions and resolution, which is relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) research.
